{
  "_meta": {
    "source": "Operand labels and glyphs pulled from the Rockwell Automation reference manuals: Logix 5000 Controllers General Instructions (publication 1756-RM003), Advanced Process Control and Drives Instructions (1756-RM006), Motion Instructions (MOTION-RM002), and GuardLogix Safety Instructions (1756-RM095).",
    "note": "Maps each instruction mnemonic to how it draws in ladder (display + form) and the operand-row labels for box instructions, in ladder operand order. Both legacy and current mnemonics are included where Logix Designer renamed an instruction (e.g. EQU/EQ, MOV/MOVE, LIM/LIMIT). Contacts/coils carry no operand labels (their tag is the label). Function-block/structured-text-only instructions are intentionally excluded (they never appear in a ladder rung). A small number of common instructions whose manual sections use combined headings (e.g. COP/CPS, JMP/LBL, JSR, GSV/SSV) were completed from standard Rockwell ladder operand names. Unknown mnemonics fall back to a generic box with positional, unlabeled operands; user-defined AOI operand names come from the parsed AOI definition, not this file."
  },
